com.cinchapi.concourse.util

Interface FixedSizeIterableByteSequences

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IterableByteSequences

    public interface FixedSizeIterableByteSequences
extends IterableByteSequences
    A IterableByteSequences object where every sequence is the same size. Therefore, it only necessary to have 4 bytes at the beginning of the collection that specifies how many sequences are present and another 4 bytes the specifies the size of each sequence once (instead of 4 bytes before every sequence in the collection).

    jnelson
